ABAKALIKI – The leadership of the Move­ment for the Actualisation of the Sovereign State of Biafra (MASSOB) has demanded for the immediate release of Nnamdi Kanu from deten­tion. The separatist group also called for the 2023 Presiden­cy of Igbo extraction, saying, “MASSOB requests Presi­dent Muhammadu Buhari to facilitate and ensure that one of the many South-East presidential aspirants suc­ceeds him in 2023 to help the country diffuse many bottled anger, which has fuelled agi­tations,” The statement, which was signed by the group’s leader, Uchenna Madu, reads: “As President Mu­hammadu Buhari visit Ebo­nyi State, MASSOB reminds Mr. President that only the release of IPOB leader will douse tension in the zone, as well as restore peaceful atmosphere to the entire country. -Advertisement- “MASSOB will not be against the visit of Pres­ident Buhari to Ebonyi State. We are making these two major demands as part of our own contributions to peace as being clam­oured by well meaning citizens. “MASSOB requests from President Muhammadu Bu­hari to facilitate and ensure that one of the many South- East presidential aspirants succeeds him in 2023 to help the country diffuse many bot­tled anger, which has fuelled agitations. “MASSOB also reminds President Muhammadu Buhari that the continuous detention of Mazi Nnamdi Kanu in DSS custody will only worsen the security challenges facing the coun­try, it will also continue to affect the economy.”